    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Fedora 19 Einrichtung]]></title>
    <link href="http://leitstelle.github.io/blog/2013/2013-11-10-fedora-start/"/>
    <updated>2013-11-10T17:06:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://leitstelle.github.io/blog/2013/fedora-start</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Konfigurieren von NVidia, Openbox, Steam, easylife-Skripten und Flash für Fedora 19.</p>

<p>Eines muss man Fedora 19 lassen: Es ist der wohl hässlichste und beschissenste Installer, den ich je benutzt habe. Am schlimmsten ist die (manuelle) Partitionierung. Man weiß gar nicht was man wo wie machen muss, damit der gewünschte Effekt dabei raus kommt. Absolut undurchsichtig.</p>

<h2>tl;dr</h2>

<ul>
<li>Konfiguriere WLAN</li>
<li>Installiere &lsquo;yum Extender&rsquo;</li>
<li>Installiere rpmfusion-Paketquellen</li>
<li>Installiere Nvidia-Treiber für die Grafikkarte</li>
<li>Installiere OpenBox

<ul>
<li>Conky, fbpanel</li>
<li>Network-Manager-Applet für ein Panel</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Installiere Flash</li>
<li>Installiere Steam</li>
<li>Installiere easylife-Skripte</li>
<li>Installiere truecrypt</li>
</ul>


<h2>Konfiguriere WLAN</h2>

<p>Beim ersten Start kann es vorkommen, dass das WLAN nicht geht.
<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Sometimes it simply helps you starting the manager. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>network-manager-applet&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Then <span class="nb">logout </span>and login again.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>Install Yum Extender, rpmfusion-Repositories und update System</h2>

<p>YumExtender ist eine schöne grafische Oberfläche für das Installationsprogramm &lsquo;yum&rsquo;. Grundsätzlich enthalten die Fedora-Paketquellen (Repositorie) nur Software aus freien Quellen ohne Beschränkungen. Leider können so viele Multimedia-Codecs, -Anwendungen und andere Programme nicht genutzt werden. Wer nicht nur freie Software verwenden möchte findet in den <a href="http://rpmfusion.org/">rpmfusion</a>-Quellen ausreichend Material.
<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum install yumex
</span><span class='line'>yum update&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Before you use new repos <span class="k">do</span> updates.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum update kernel&lt;em&gt; selinux-policy&lt;/em&gt;
</span><span class='line'>reboot&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Add rpm fusion repositories.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum localinstall <span class="p">&amp;</span>ndash<span class="p">;</span>nogpgcheck &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://download1.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-$&quot;</span>&gt;http://download1.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-<span class="nv">$&lt;</span>/a&gt;<span class="o">(</span>rpm -E %fedora<span class="o">)</span>.noarch.rpm
</span><span class='line'>yum localinstall <span class="p">&amp;</span>ndash<span class="p">;</span>nogpgcheck &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://download1.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$&quot;</span>&gt;http://download1.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-<span class="nv">$&lt;</span>/a&gt;<span class="o">(</span>rpm -E %fedora<span class="o">)</span>.noarch.rpm
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>Installation des Nvidia-Treiber</h2>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Check your video card.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;lspci <span class="p">|</span>grep -i VGA&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Example output:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;01:00.0 VGA compatible controller: NVIDIA Corporation GT216M <span class="o">[</span>GeForce GT 240M<span class="o">]</span> <span class="o">(</span>rev a2<span class="o">)</span>&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;If some Intel graphics controller is also shown, be carefully, <span class="nb">read </span>in otherer forums&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<p>Nun installiere den Treiber. Gehe dabei ganz sicher, dass du die richtige Version für deine Grafikkarte verwendest. Im nächsten Schritt musst du dich für &lsquo;akmod&rsquo; oder &lsquo;kmod&rsquo; entscheiden. Der Wesentliche Unterschied ist, dass mittels &lsquo;akmod&rsquo; die Treiber für deinen Kernel bei jedem Kernel-Update mit neu einkompiliert werden. Verzichte darauf, wenn du eh nur Kernel aus dem Repository verwendest. Denn &lsquo;kmod&rsquo; bietet die passenden Treiber für den Kernel aus dem Repo.</p>

<h3>AKMOD</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
<span class='line-number'>14</span>
<span class='line-number'>15</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;akmod-nvidia <span class="k">for</span> GeForce 8/9/200/300/400/500/600/700 series cards.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum install akmod-nvidia xorg-x11-drv-nvidia&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;akmod-nvidia-304xx <span class="k">for</span> GeForce 6/7 series cards.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;yum install akmod-nvidia-304xx xorg-x11-drv-nvidia-304xx-libs&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;If you use kernel PAE.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;yum install kernel-PAE-devel&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>KMOD</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;kmod-nvidia <span class="k">for</span> GeForce 8/9/200/300/400/500/600/700 series cards&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum install kmod-nvidia xorg-x11-drv-nvidia-libs&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;kmod-nvidia-304xx <span class="k">for</span> GeForce 6/7 series cards&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;yum install kmod-nvidia-304xx xorg-x11-drv-nvidia-304xx-libs&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>VDPAU-Unterstützung</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Video acceleration VDPAU/VAAPI support <span class="o">(</span>GeForce <span class="m">8</span> and later<span class="o">)</span>.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum install vdpauinfo libva-vdpau-driver libva-utils
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>Deinstallation des alten NVidia-Treiber (nouveau)</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum remove xorg-x11-drv-nouveau
</span><span class='line'>nvidia-xconfig
</span><span class='line'>reboot
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>Problemlösung</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>In case of some problems try this. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Without reboot:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;init 3
</span><span class='line'>nvidia-config-display <span class="nb">enable</span>
</span><span class='line'>init 5&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Or in <span class="k">case</span> of some other problems try:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;/usr/sbin/nvidia-config-display disable
</span><span class='line'>/usr/sbin/nvidia-config-display <span class="nb">enable</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>Deinstallation</h3>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Uninstall all nvidia driver. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum remove xorg-x11-drv-nvidia* nvidia-settings nvidia-xconfig
</span><span class='line'>yum install xorg-x11-drv-nouveau
</span><span class='line'>reboot
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>Installiere OpenBox</h2>

<p>Ich verwende als minimalisitschen Windowmanager gern Openbox. Als Panel <a href="https://admin.fedoraproject.org/pkgdb/acls/name/fbpanel">fbpanel</a>(<a href="http://fbpanel.sourceforge.net">fbpanel.sourceforge.net</a>) und als Systemmonitor <a href="https://admin.fedoraproject.org/pkgdb/acls/name/conky">conky</a>(<a href="http://conky.sourceforge.net/">conky.sourceforge.net</a>). Es kommt häufiger vor, dass man Probleme hat text zu markieren  (Markierung und Text selber sind schwarz). Abhilfe schafft hier häufig den &lsquo;<a href="https://admin.fedoraproject.org/pkgdb/acls/name/gnome-settings-daemon">gnome-settings-daemon</a>&rsquo;(<a href="https://git.gnome.org/browse/gnome-settings-daemon">git.gnome.org</a>) zu starten, sofern installiert.
<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum install openbox conky fbpanel&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Network manager applet&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum install network-manager-applet
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>Installiere Flash-Plugin</h2>

<p><a href="https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Flash">Flash</a> als Paketquelle für Fedora bereit gestellt.
<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;64bit.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;yum install &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://linuxdownload.adobe.com/adobe-release/adobe-release-x86_64-1.0-1.noarch.rpm&quot;</span>&gt;http://linuxdownload.adobe.com/adobe-release/adobe-release-x86_64-1.0-1.noarch.rpm&lt;/a&gt; -y&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;32bit.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;yum install &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://linuxdownload.adobe.com/adobe-release/adobe-release-i386-1.0-1.noarch.rpm&quot;</span>&gt;http://linuxdownload.adobe.com/adobe-release/adobe-release-i386-1.0-1.noarch.rpm&lt;/a&gt; -y&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;rpm <span class="p">&amp;</span>ndash<span class="p">;</span>import /etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-adobe-linux
</span><span class='line'>yum install flash-plugin -y
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>Installiere Steam</h2>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum -y <span class="p">&amp;</span>ndash<span class="p">;</span><span class="nv">enablerepo</span><span class="o">=</span>rpmfusion-nonfree-updates-testing install steam&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Reboot or Relogin&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;service gdm restart
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>
Siehe auch <a href="http://linuxmotion.com/tutorials/97-install-steam-in-fedora-19">hier</a>.</p>

<h2>easylife-Skripte</h2>

<p>Um sich die Sache zu vereinfachen kann die Skriptsammlung &lsquo;easy life&rsquo; verwendet werden.
<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -  &lt;br/&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://sourceforge.net/projects/easylife-linux/files/easyLife/&quot;</span>&gt;http://sourceforge.net/projects/easylife-linux/files/easyLife/&lt;/a&gt;
</span><span class='line'>wget -O easylife-4.0-2.noarch.rpm &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://sourceforge.net/projects/easylife-linux/files/easyLife/4.0-2%20for%20Fedora%2019/easylife-4.0-2.noarch.rpm/download&quot;</span>&gt;http://sourceforge.net/projects/easylife-linux/files/easyLife/4.0-2%20for%20Fedora%2019/easylife-4.0-2.noarch.rpm/download&lt;/a&gt;
</span><span class='line'>rpm -Uvh easylife-4.0-2.noarch.rpm
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h2>truecrypt in die sudoers-Liste</h2>

<p><a href="/blog/2013/2013-11-19-install-truecrypt/">Installiere</a> truecrypt, dann richte die Benutzung ohne root-Privilegiene ein:
<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Configure truecrypt usage without admin privileges. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>su -
</span><span class='line'>yum install sudo&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Die Zeile <span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>Defaults requiretty<span class="p">&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span> in der sudoers-Liste auskommentieren:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;sed -i <span class="p">&amp;</span>rsquo<span class="p">;</span>s/Defaults    requiretty/#Defaults    requiretty/<span class="p">&amp;</span>lsquo<span class="p">;</span> /etc/sudoers&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;truecrypt hinzufügen&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;echo <span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>username <span class="nv">ALL</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">(</span>root<span class="o">)</span> NOPASSWD:/usr/bin/truecrypt<span class="p">&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span> &gt;&gt; /etc/sudoers
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>
]]></content>
